olive oil
1 packet herbed pork sausage
½ tin sweetcorn
2 brioche hotdog buns
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet Chargrilled Capsicum Relish

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Place herbed pork sausages on a lined oven tray, drizzle with olive oil and turn to coat.
• Bake until cooked through, 12-16 minutes.

• Meanwhile, drain sweetcorn (see ingredients).
• Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook corn kernels until lightly browned, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a medium bowl.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the kernels are ‘popping’ out.

• Slice brioche hotdog buns in half lengthways, three quarters of the way through.
• Bake buns directly on a wire oven rack until heated through, 5-7 minutes.
• To the bowl with corn, add shredded cabbage mix, mixed salad leaves and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

• Spread each hot dog bun base with garlic aioli and fill with two pork sausages, chargrilled capsicum relish and cabbage salad.
• Divide pork sausage and capsicum relish hot dogs between plates.
• Serve with remaining salad. Enjoy!